title: LEGCO QUESTION NO.8 (Written Reply)
question_text: Question: In connection with the recruitment of Dental Hygienists, will the Government inform this Council : (a) of the entry qualifications for the post of Dental Hygienists; (b) of the number of Dental Hygienist recruitment exercises conducted over the past three years, and the respective numbers of vacancies and eligible applicants in each of these recruitment exercises; (c) of the difficulties in recruiting such staff; and (d) whether it has taken any measures to attract more qualified persons to join the grade; if so, of the details?
reply_text:
(a) The entry requirements for the post of Dental Hygienists are as follows :
The person concerned should -
(i) have enrolled with the Dental Council of Hong Kong under Ancillary Dental Workers (Dental Hygienists) Regulations (CAP. 156, sub. leg. B), to practise as a dental hygienist; and
(ii) have Chinese Language and English Language (Syllabus B) at Grade ‘E’ or above in the Hong Kong Certificate of Examination, or equivalent; and

above in the Hong Kong Certificate of Examination, or equivalent; and
(iii) be able to speak fluent English and Cantonese. (b) The Department of Health conducted recruitment exercises in January 1995, February 1996 and February 1998. The vacancies were 2, 1 and 2 respectively and the numbers of qualified applicants were 4, 5 and 7 respectively. (c)&(d) In these three recruitment exercises, all vacancies were filled by suitable persons selected from a pool of qualified applicants two to five times the numbers of vacancies. The Department of

pool of qualified applicants two to five times the numbers of vacancies. The Department of Health was satisfied with the result of these recruitment exercises.
